    <h2 class="odd">IMPORT FORMS (Liaise or eForms)</h2>
    <div class="even marg10 boxshadow1">
        <p>There is an import utility to allow importing forms from the XOOPS Liaise
            or XOOPS eForms modules.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="odd" id="checkbox_element">Import Instructions</h3>
    <div class="even marg10 boxshadow1">
        <p>The following instructions outline the procedures to import forms from one of the supported modules.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Turn off your XOOPS site: Admin -> Preferences -> System Options -> General Settings</li>
            <li>Make sure Liaise (or eForms) module is active</li>
            <li>Navigate to xForms Admin -> Import tab</li>
            <li>Select the import link for the desired module to import</li>
            <li>Navigate to imported form(s) and ensure permissions are set as you want.</li>
            <li>Turn on your XOOPS site</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
